summary: Phan theories:
body:
Phan theories:

Ok, i know a LOT of people ship Phan, and i do to, platonically. There are some Phan theories that are reasonable and some that are far from it. I wish people would understand that if they’re dating then we’ll be happy, and if they’re not then we should support them because admit it, you crave a friendship like theirs. Think about this, if we somehow convince one that they like the other and they get together, what happens if they were to break up? They need each other because they care for each other. That would cause awkward tension and not something any of us or either of them would enjoy. So seriously, can y’all stop with the theories, and just enjoy that they’re friends? If they’re together they’ll tell us and if their not then you should appreciate them because they are the freaking best things that have ever happened to me, and probably to most of you. I’m not against shipping, just don’t take it too far.


Thank you for your time

summary: To honour the birthday of Tove Jansson (9 August 1914 - 27 June 2001), the creator of the Moomins, I present you this drawing of...
caption:
To honour the birthday of Tove Jansson (9 August 1914 - 27 June 2001), the creator of the Moomins, I present you this drawing of @danielhowell and @amazingphil as Moomins I made for a friend’s birthday card back in May.

I never do art (this actually started as a sketch for a cross-stitch project), but sometimes you just go beyond what you know for the people you care about.
